    </div>

    <p>The narrative surrounding the global economy's transition to renewable energy often focuses on high-tech solutions, but the reality is grounded in physical commodities. Copper is the indispensable element of electrification. From electric vehicle (EV) charging networks to upgraded electrical grids and wind turbine manufacturing, the demand for this highly conductive metal is projected to skyrocket through 2025 and into 2026. Conversely, new mine supply takes years—often decades—to come online, creating a structural supply-demand deficit that presents a compelling opportunity for investors.</p>
